{\an8}♪

100
00:04:05.278 --> 00:04:07.380
{\an8}♪

101
00:04:22.795 --> 00:04:25.131
(music fades out)

102
00:04:26.766 --> 00:04:29.902
(ominous music playing)

103
00:04:30.536 --> 00:04:32.639
(door creaking)

104
00:04:39.779 --> 00:04:41.948
(footsteps echoing)

105
00:04:49.656 --> 00:04:53.126
(woman speaking High
Valyrian. voice echoing)

106
00:05:01.100 --> 00:05:02.001
What?

107
00:05:02.002 --> 00:05:04.837
(High Valyrian continues)

108
00:05:06.939 --> 00:05:08.875
I can't understand.

109
00:05:13.179 --> 00:05:15.948
(speaking High Valyrian)

110
00:05:19.752 --> 00:05:21.487
Speak plainly.

111
00:05:26.993 --> 00:05:28.061
{\an8}Stop.

112
00:05:28.828 --> 00:05:30.196
{\an8}Stop it.

113
00:05:38.838 --> 00:05:41.073
(tense music playing)

114
00:05:41.074 --> 00:05:43.376
(crown clattering)

115
00:05:46.379 --> 00:05:48.481
(sword falls)

116
00:05:54.854 --> 00:05:56.923
♪

117
00:06:02.028 --> 00:06:05.064
- (distorted) There's been a raven.
- (door opens)

118
00:06:08.501 --> 00:06:11.336
Simon Strong: Good
morrow. Your Grace.

119
00:06:11.337 --> 00:06:14.240
Slept well. I trust?

120
00:06:14.574 --> 00:06:17.243
As I said. there's been a raven.

121
00:06:19.345 --> 00:06:22.748
Aegon's army departed King's
Landing a fortnight ago.

122
00:06:22.749 --> 00:06:25.884
The castles of
Rosby and Stokeworth

123
00:06:25.885 --> 00:06:27.652
have both fallen without siege.

124
00:06:27.653 --> 00:06:29.955
They have raised Aegon's banner

125
00:06:29.956 --> 00:06:33.693
and added their levies to
Ser Criston Cole's host.

126
00:06:34.527 --> 00:06:36.995
Both houses cited that

127
00:06:36.996 --> 00:06:40.933
sad business with the usurper's
son in their declarations.

128
00:06:41.901 --> 00:06:44.102
Ser Criston's army.

129
00:06:44.103 --> 00:06:46.538
now tripled in strength.

130
00:06:46.539 --> 00:06:49.307
might have Harrenhal
as its destination.

131
00:06:49.308 --> 00:06:52.778
- (goat bleats) - Even if you
can raise a host of Rivermen.

132
00:06:52.779 --> 00:06:56.048
they will not be ready
in time to face him.

133
00:07:01.988 --> 00:07:05.091
Let's see what your Lord
Paramount is made of.

134
00:07:06.192 --> 00:07:07.660
(sighs)

135
00:07:10.563 --> 00:07:13.899
(stammers) My prince...
Uh. My-My Grace.

136
00:07:13.900 --> 00:07:15.334
Your Grace.

137
00:07:16.068 --> 00:07:19.304
Lord Grover is looking more hale
and healthy than I expected.

138
00:07:19.305 --> 00:07:20.839
Uh. this is Ser Oscar Tully.

139
00:07:20.840 --> 00:07:22.107
grandson to Grover Tully.

140
00:07:22.108 --> 00:07:23.675
He is heir to Riverrun

141
00:07:23.676 --> 00:07:26.812
and the future Lord
Paramount of the Riverlands.

142
00:07:26.813 --> 00:07:30.215
His Grace. the King
Consort. Daemon Targaryen.

143
00:07:30.216 --> 00:07:33.752
- Oscar Tully: It is an honor. Your Grace.
- Daemon Targaryen: Indeed.

144
00:07:33.753 --> 00:07:35.922
(sword clatters)

145
00:07:39.592 --> 00:07:41.828
How fares your grandsire?

146
00:07:45.598 --> 00:07:48.867
Sadly. he remains incapacitated.

147
00:07:48.868 --> 00:07:51.536
He lies in a kind
of waking sleep.

148
00:07:51.537 --> 00:07:55.106
unable to do much more
than take meager drink.

149
00:07:55.107 --> 00:07:57.809
It is barely enough
to sustain him.

150
00:07:57.810 --> 00:07:59.678
So. he's alive?

151
00:07:59.679 --> 00:08:01.913
Yes. gods be good.

152
00:08:01.914 --> 00:08:04.649
Well. my time is short and
I have need of an army.

153
00:08:04.650 --> 00:08:07.018
Perhaps you might place a
feather pillow over his head

154
00:08:07.019 --> 00:08:09.522
and speed along
your inheritance?

155
00:08:11.390 --> 00:08:15.127
I-I love my grandsire.
like a father.

156
00:08:15.695 --> 00:08:19.565
My own lord father died
suddenly. himself a young man.

157
00:08:20.099 --> 00:08:22.767
Lord Grover raised
me in his stead.

158
00:08:22.768 --> 00:08:24.002
All very touching.

159
00:08:24.003 --> 00:08:26.071
Are you here to speak with
your grandsire's voice?

160
00:08:26.072 --> 00:08:28.139
For House Tully
and the Riverlands?

161
00:08:28.140 --> 00:08:29.842
While he still lives?

162
00:08:32.245 --> 00:08:36.148
- That is not our way.
- Then you're of no use to me.

163
00:08:36.682 --> 00:08:38.550
I can see why the
Blackwoods and the Brackens

164
00:08:38.551 --> 00:08:39.818
did not fear to start a war

165
00:08:39.819 --> 00:08:42.220
beneath the nose of
their liege lords.

166
00:08:42.221 --> 00:08:44.523
House Tully is a
fish with no head.

167
00:08:44.524 --> 00:08:46.858
Remind me which
of your countrymen

168
00:08:46.859 --> 00:08:48.527
claim to fight in
the name of Aegon?

169
00:08:48.528 --> 00:08:50.629
Was it. was it
Bracken or Blackwood?

170
00:08:50.630 --> 00:08:53.498
It was House Bracken that
declared Green. Your Grace.

171
00:08:53.499 --> 00:08:54.901
Who could remember.

172
00:08:55.935 --> 00:08:56.903
Summon the Blackwoods here.

173
00:08:56.904 --> 00:08:57.969
I require men of action

174
00:08:57.970 --> 00:09:00.139
to lead my host of Rivermen.

175
00:09:00.473 --> 00:09:03.276
(tense music playing)

176
00:09:07.013 --> 00:09:09.148
(indistinct chatter)

177
00:09:09.482 --> 00:09:11.584
(dog barking)

178
00:09:14.353 --> 00:09:16.422
♪

179
00:09:23.029 --> 00:09:25.131
(birds cawing)

180
00:09:29.001 --> 00:09:30.469
M'lady.

181
00:09:33.773 --> 00:09:37.576
"Princess." if we're
holding to formalities.

182
00:09:37.577 --> 00:09:40.413
Apologies. Princess.

183
00:09:41.681 --> 00:09:44.082
And you are Alyn.

184
00:09:44.083 --> 00:09:46.452
Yes. Princess.

185
00:09:47.587 --> 00:09:49.321
I'm given to understand
my lord husband

186
00:09:49.322 --> 00:09:51.324
owes you his life.

187
00:09:54.260 --> 00:09:57.630
But I was not told his
savior was so comely.

188
00:09:58.631 --> 00:10:01.132
Your mother must've
been very beautiful.

189
00:10:01.133 --> 00:10:03.736
- Corlys Velaryon: Rhaenys.
- (clears throat)

190
00:10:11.010 --> 00:10:13.813
- Is your work finished?
- No. m'lord.

191
00:10:17.016 --> 00:10:19.151
(indistinct chatter)

192
00:10:24.523 --> 00:10:26.792
I just had a word
with your captains.

193
00:10:28.561 --> 00:10:32.264
He was the sailor who plucked
you from your watery grave?

194
00:10:33.332 --> 00:10:35.434
(birds cawing)

195
00:10:39.839 --> 00:10:40.873
Yes.

196
00:10:42.208 --> 00:10:44.043
You did not think to mention it?

197
00:10:44.844 --> 00:10:46.779
I did not think it relevant.

198
00:10:48.881 --> 00:10:51.050
I know who he is. Corlys.

199
00:10:53.252 --> 00:10:56.888
Alyn's past is no fault of his.

200
00:10:56.889 --> 00:10:57.956
He saved his lord's life.

201
00:10:57.957 --> 00:10:59.290
He should be raised
up and honored.

202
00:10:59.291 --> 00:11:00.625
not hidden beneath the tides.

203
00:11:00.626 --> 00:11:02.828
Is this why you came?

204
00:11:03.729 --> 00:11:05.665
To subject me to an inquisition?

205
00:11:07.533 --> 00:11:11.569
I came to tell you that Baela
has called me to Dragonstone.

206
00:11:11.570 --> 00:11:12.905
Baela?

207
00:11:13.806 --> 00:11:16.474
That council is going to dine
on her and Jace for supper.

208
00:11:16.475 --> 00:11:18.643
They grow restless in
Rhaenyra's absence.

209
00:11:18.644 --> 00:11:22.013
Still... Where has
that woman gone?

210
00:11:22.014 --> 00:11:25.985
I suspect to try and draw
us all back from the abyss.

211
00:11:37.997 --> 00:11:40.866
- (knocks at door)
- (Alicent sighs)

212
00:11:43.302 --> 00:11:45.404
(distant chatter)

213
00:11:47.707 --> 00:11:51.243
- Good morrow. Your Grace.
- Good morrow. Grand Maester.

214
00:11:54.947 --> 00:11:57.415
As requested.

215
00:11:57.416 --> 00:12:01.019
- I brewed it myself.
- Thank you.

216
00:12:01.020 --> 00:12:03.389
I will see it
delivered discreetly.

217
00:12:04.557 --> 00:12:08.760
Do report if the recipient
has need of any remedy.

218
00:12:08.761 --> 00:12:11.363
The tea is known to
disagree with the gut.

219
00:12:12.031 --> 00:12:14.433
I shall observe
the girl closely.

220
00:12:15.801 --> 00:12:17.903
(birds chirping)

221
00:12:20.873 --> 00:12:22.608
Grand Maester.

222
00:12:28.447 --> 00:12:30.815
You've ever been
a practical man.

223
00:12:30.816 --> 00:12:33.352
an honorable servant
to the crown.

224
00:12:33.986 --> 00:12:37.423
And you served my lord
husband in his darkest hours.

225
00:12:37.790 --> 00:12:40.159
Such was my duty. Your Grace.

226
00:12:41.527 --> 00:12:42.795
Tell me.

227
00:12:44.797 --> 00:12:48.066
Do you believe Viserys
wanted Aegon to succeed him?

228
00:12:48.067 --> 00:12:50.236
(birds chirping)

229
00:12:52.538 --> 00:12:54.840
I could not know.

230
00:12:56.542 --> 00:12:59.779
His Grace never raised
the matter with me.

231
00:13:12.291 --> 00:13:14.426
(distant chatter)

232
00:13:15.594 --> 00:13:17.696
(door closes)

233
00:13:18.497 --> 00:13:21.634
(tense music playing)

234
00:13:39.118 --> 00:13:41.187
♪

235
00:13:44.723 --> 00:13:46.192
(groans)

236
00:13:51.564 --> 00:13:53.032
(groans)

237
00:13:54.166 --> 00:13:55.668
(coughs)

238
00:13:59.171 --> 00:14:00.538
Baela Targaryen: Ser
Criston Cole's host

239
00:14:00.539 --> 00:14:02.240
has taken to exploiting
the tree cover

240
00:14:02.241 --> 00:14:03.541
to conceal its movements.

241
00:14:03.542 --> 00:14:05.210
He now only travels by night

242
00:14:05.211 --> 00:14:06.444
to confound our dragons.

243
00:14:06.445 --> 00:14:08.413
Bartimos Celtigar: And
what is Cole's heading?

244
00:14:08.414 --> 00:14:09.981
It is difficult to say.
but there were signs

245
00:14:09.982 --> 00:14:13.084
of an army moving
northwest. I believe.

246
00:14:13.085 --> 00:14:14.485
Gormon Massey:
(laughs) She believes.

247
00:14:14.486 --> 00:14:16.654
You should've burned them
when you had the chance.

248
00:14:16.655 --> 00:14:17.755
Perhaps you can. Ser Alfred.

249
00:14:17.756 --> 00:14:19.324
when you next sight
them on your dragon.

250
00:14:19.325 --> 00:14:22.794
- (slight chuckle) - The only
reason we know any of this

251
00:14:22.795 --> 00:14:24.362
is because of Baela's efforts.

252
00:14:24.363 --> 00:14:25.997
Bartimos: What do
we know. my prince?

253
00:14:25.998 --> 00:14:28.333
If you ask me. it
is little and less.

254
00:14:28.334 --> 00:14:31.202
We know that Cole possesses a
host that is growing in strength

255
00:14:31.203 --> 00:14:32.470
and that it is a problem.

256
00:14:32.471 --> 00:14:33.938
Gormon: Can Daemon
hope to meet it

257
00:14:33.939 --> 00:14:35.440
with his own in time?

258
00:14:35.441 --> 00:14:36.574
And if I know the Riverlands.

259
00:14:36.575 --> 00:14:38.710
he has more disentangling
ahead of him

260
00:14:38.711 --> 00:14:41.880
than the end of a Lyseni orgy.

261
00:14:41.881 --> 00:14:45.618
Have you heard word
from your father?

262
00:14:47.887 --> 00:14:51.456
- No.
- Maester Gerardys: Ravens were sent to Harrenhal

263
00:14:51.457 --> 00:14:54.692
seeking news of Daemon's
progress with the Riverlords.

264
00:14:54.693 --> 00:14:57.161
None have. as yet. returned.

265
00:14:57.162 --> 00:14:58.763
Alfred Broome: Just so.

266
00:14:58.764 --> 00:15:01.132
An enemy host. growing
in constitution.

267
00:15:01.133 --> 00:15:06.004
marches somewhere in the
vastness of the Crownlands.

268
00:15:06.005 --> 00:15:09.807
We could. perhaps. act if
only we had a host of our own.

269
00:15:09.808 --> 00:15:11.377
Or someone here to lead us.

270
00:15:11.877 --> 00:15:13.913
Mind your tongue. Ser Alfred.

271
00:15:15.214 --> 00:15:17.649
Does it speak
falsely. my prince?

272
00:15:17.650 --> 00:15:20.051
This council is rudderless.

273
00:15:20.052 --> 00:15:22.588
I'm doing my best to
steer it. Ser Alfred.

274
00:15:23.889 --> 00:15:27.625
Why should your voice be any
louder than ours. Princess?

275
00:15:27.626 --> 00:15:29.460
The queen did not name you Hand.

276
00:15:29.461 --> 00:15:31.930
It is her voice. and
that of the king consort.

277
00:15:31.931 --> 00:15:35.166
that we need to raise alliances
and command our vassals.

278
00:15:35.167 --> 00:15:38.771
- But they are gone.
- Corlys: What has come of this council?

279
00:15:39.438 --> 00:15:40.739
(soft gasp)

280
00:15:43.742 --> 00:15:45.244
My lord.

281
00:15:48.080 --> 00:15:51.349
Our enemy is on the march.

282
00:15:51.350 --> 00:15:53.551
Is there naught to be done
in the absence of the queen.

283
00:15:53.552 --> 00:15:56.988
but to grouse and
claw for power?

284
00:15:56.989 --> 00:15:58.991
(Bartimos sighs)

285
00:16:02.995 --> 00:16:06.497
We do not know the
queen's doings.

286
00:16:06.498 --> 00:16:09.100
But we must trust that
she seeks the same

287
00:16:09.101 --> 00:16:11.370
as each of us at this table.

288
00:16:12.871 --> 00:16:15.441
An end to this conflict.

289
00:16:17.343 --> 00:16:20.779
- (rain pattering)
- (tense music playing)

290
00:16:21.947 --> 00:16:24.049
(birds cawing)

291
00:16:28.821 --> 00:16:30.956
(indistinct shouting)

292
00:16:34.460 --> 00:16:36.995
(distant yell)

293
00:16:36.996 --> 00:16:39.464
Criston Cole: Men
of House Darklyn.

294
00:16:39.465 --> 00:16:43.869
All who bend the knee to the
true king. Aegon. will be spared.

295
00:16:44.737 --> 00:16:47.472
You can earn back your
honor by raising his banner

296
00:16:47.473 --> 00:16:49.307
and fighting in his name

297
00:16:49.308 --> 00:16:52.177
against the Whore
of Dragonstone.

298
00:16:53.012 --> 00:16:55.147
All who refuse...

299
00:16:56.448 --> 00:16:58.584
will have their death.

300
00:17:00.219 --> 00:17:02.755
♪

301
00:17:12.498 --> 00:17:14.199
Good morrow. Lord Darklyn.

302
00:17:14.800 --> 00:17:18.269
Is there no honor left
in this world. Cole?

303
00:17:18.270 --> 00:17:20.304
Sacking your queen's own castles

304
00:17:20.305 --> 00:17:23.207
and putting her
people to the sword?

305
00:17:23.208 --> 00:17:25.010
"Kingmaker."

306
00:17:29.114 --> 00:17:31.750
You are not fit for
the white cloak.

307
00:17:33.152 --> 00:17:34.952
♪

308
00:17:34.953 --> 00:17:38.223
This is a better death
than a traitor deserves.

309
00:17:38.624 --> 00:17:40.959
You should thank me for it.

310
00:17:42.961 --> 00:17:46.098
Yours will come in kind.

311
00:17:48.133 --> 00:17:49.401
(grunts)

312
00:17:51.770 --> 00:17:53.872
(horse neighs)

313
00:17:57.009 --> 00:17:59.078
♪

314
00:18:00.579 --> 00:18:01.880
Lord Hand.

315
00:18:17.162 --> 00:18:19.397
We'll lead the van northeast.

316
00:18:19.398 --> 00:18:20.898
follow the coastline.

317
00:18:20.899 --> 00:18:22.233
(horse neighs)

318
00:18:22.234 --> 00:18:23.868
I realize you were
neither born nor bred

319
00:18:23.869 --> 00:18:27.305
anywhere near the Crownlands.
my good Lord Hand.

320
00:18:27.306 --> 00:18:29.975
but Harrenhal is to the west.

321
00:18:33.912 --> 00:18:35.647
Indeed it is.

322
00:18:38.250 --> 00:18:41.552
Fuck you. I told you we
should've sent our dragons.

323
00:18:41.553 --> 00:18:43.455
And now look what's happened.

324
00:18:43.789 --> 00:18:46.591
Daemon. of all people.
has taken Harrenhal.

325
00:18:46.592 --> 00:18:49.160
I give you a job. and
now you just sit there.

326
00:18:49.161 --> 00:18:51.797
It's your fucking castle!

327
00:18:53.265 --> 00:18:57.468
Well. that castle is more
crippled than I am. Your Grace.

328
00:18:57.469 --> 00:18:58.636
(scoffs)

329
00:18:58.637 --> 00:19:00.104
It's like to drive
Daemon to madness

330
00:19:00.105 --> 00:19:01.539
as he attempts to
make use of it.

331
00:19:01.540 --> 00:19:03.976
It is beyond his faculties.

332
00:19:04.610 --> 00:19:08.646
It is also penniless. as I
happily control all of its gold.

333
00:19:08.647 --> 00:19:12.250
So. as Harrenhal saps
Daemon's resolve.

334
00:19:12.251 --> 00:19:14.652
the false queen remains
trapped on her island.

335
00:19:14.653 --> 00:19:18.189
and Ser Criston continues felling
castles in the Crownlands.

336
00:19:18.190 --> 00:19:20.259
(stammers) Wh...

337
00:19:20.626 --> 00:19:23.361
I need to be informed
of these things

338
00:19:23.362 --> 00:19:24.962
if I am to make
informed rulings.

339
00:19:24.963 --> 00:19:26.797
I will not be made to
look a fool in front of

340
00:19:26.798 --> 00:19:29.835
- my allies and enemies.
- Aemond Targaryen: Harrenhal must wait.

341
00:19:33.172 --> 00:19:35.807
Ser Criston is marching
on Rook's Rest.

342
00:19:36.408 --> 00:19:38.042
Rook's Re... A pathetic prize.

343
00:19:38.043 --> 00:19:40.512
- I gave no such command...
- The castle is small.

344
00:19:41.580 --> 00:19:42.747
weakly defended.

345
00:19:42.748 --> 00:19:45.950
and Lord Staunton sits
on Rhaenyra's council.

346
00:19:45.951 --> 00:19:48.019
After Cole smashes it.

347
00:19:48.020 --> 00:19:50.689
we'll have Dragonstone
effectively cut off by land.

348
00:19:52.157 --> 00:19:54.892
This war will not be
won with dragons alone.

349
00:19:54.893 --> 00:19:58.029
but with dragons flying
behind armies of men.

350
00:19:58.030 --> 00:20:03.034
No! Have him turn about.
I want Harrenhal back.

351
00:20:03.035 --> 00:20:05.537
Cole is already
preparing his attack.

352
00:20:06.805 --> 00:20:08.806
Uh. how-how do you know this?

353
00:20:08.807 --> 00:20:11.043
Aemond: He sent word to me.

354
00:20:11.944 --> 00:20:13.212
To you?

355
00:20:15.847 --> 00:20:18.183
The two of you have been

356
00:20:18.550 --> 00:20:22.987
plotting... without
my authority?

357
00:20:22.988 --> 00:20:24.356
(sighs)

358
00:20:26.658 --> 00:20:29.428
{\an8}(speaking High Valyrian)

359
00:20:43.642 --> 00:20:44.776
Mm.

360
00:21:02.327 --> 00:21:04.429
(birds cawing)

361
00:21:07.866 --> 00:21:10.636
{\an8}(speaking High Valyrian)

362
00:21:18.410 --> 00:21:19.478
Mm.

363
00:21:21.747 --> 00:21:23.915
(councilmember clears throat)

364
00:21:25.284 --> 00:21:27.418
Harrenhal is a useful morass.

365
00:21:27.419 --> 00:21:30.488
It will keep Daemon well-occupied
while we strengthen our host

366
00:21:30.489 --> 00:21:32.757
and weaken Rhaenyra's
support on the mainland.

367
00:21:32.758 --> 00:21:35.760
We will deal with it in
the Riverlands in time.

368
00:21:35.761 --> 00:21:40.264
But right now. Rook's
Rest is an easy target

369
00:21:40.265 --> 00:21:42.467
and a worthy effort.

370
00:21:43.368 --> 00:21:46.337
Don't you agree. my king?

371
00:21:46.338 --> 00:21:49.541
(tense music playing)

372
00:21:57.182 --> 00:21:59.283
(knocks on door)

373
00:21:59.284 --> 00:22:02.521
- (heavy breathing)
- Come.

374
00:22:06.825 --> 00:22:08.527
Lord Larys.

375
00:22:12.164 --> 00:22:14.198
I thought I'd look in
on you. Your Grace.

376
00:22:14.199 --> 00:22:17.201
after your absence
from the small council.

377
00:22:17.202 --> 00:22:19.170
I feared something was amiss.

378
00:22:19.171 --> 00:22:22.273
(sighs) You're kind
to do so. my lord.

379
00:22:22.274 --> 00:22:24.775
but indulgence was my sin.

380
00:22:24.776 --> 00:22:28.212
I... ventured into the lamprey
pie at last night's supper.

381
00:22:28.213 --> 00:22:30.114
Too far. I fear.

382
00:22:30.115 --> 00:22:32.317
(heavy breathing)

383
00:22:33.251 --> 00:22:35.020
Larys Strong: Mm.

384
00:22:36.588 --> 00:22:39.057
That is a rich indulgence.

385
00:22:39.758 --> 00:22:43.361
But I believe it is a sin
to deny your appetites.

386
00:22:43.362 --> 00:22:46.898
They are what make us
fully alive as mortal men.

387
00:22:50.936 --> 00:22:53.437
Was anything of note
discussed at the council?

388
00:22:53.438 --> 00:22:55.339
Daemon having seized Harrenhal

389
00:22:55.340 --> 00:22:58.109
and His Grace's
resulting displeasure.

390
00:22:58.110 --> 00:23:03.147
I would've thought you would
be the most aggrieved. my lord.

391
00:23:03.148 --> 00:23:05.617
I see it as a loss
for our greater good.

392
00:23:06.952 --> 00:23:09.253
Dragonstone's attentions
are greatly divided.

393
00:23:09.254 --> 00:23:12.758
First in the Riverlands and the
Gullet. and now the Crownlands.

394
00:23:13.558 --> 00:23:15.426
Ser Criston wins every
challenge he faces there.

395
00:23:15.427 --> 00:23:19.097
That truth alone is like
to incite Rhaenyra's fury.

396
00:23:19.698 --> 00:23:22.567
He's covered himself
in glory. to be sure.

397
00:23:23.535 --> 00:23:26.238
And you must worry for him?

398
00:23:26.538 --> 00:23:28.874
Your sworn sword...

399
00:23:29.775 --> 00:23:31.442
on the march.

400
00:23:31.443 --> 00:23:32.710
ever exposed to dragons?

401
00:23:32.711 --> 00:23:34.880
It is a perilous road.

402
00:23:38.049 --> 00:23:40.218
Ser Criston is the
Hand of the King.

403
00:23:41.286 --> 00:23:44.222
We should all pray for his
victory and safe return.

404
00:23:45.223 --> 00:23:46.491
Indeed.

405
00:23:47.993 --> 00:23:50.961
(sighs. inhales)

406
00:23:50.962 --> 00:23:54.232
- (Larys grunts)
- (Alicent sighs)

407
00:23:56.268 --> 00:23:59.905
If I may be so bold. my queen...

408
00:24:05.377 --> 00:24:08.013
you have not seemed
yourself of late.

409
00:24:09.314 --> 00:24:11.715
Only weeks ago. my
lord husband was alive

410
00:24:11.716 --> 00:24:13.752
and the realm was at peace.

411
00:24:14.119 --> 00:24:17.955
Now. I've... barely had the
hours to grieve one tragedy

412
00:24:17.956 --> 00:24:18.989
before suffering the next.

413
00:24:18.990 --> 00:24:22.961
I regret if I have
not been myself.

414
00:24:24.963 --> 00:24:25.963
Hm.

415
00:24:26.231 --> 00:24:29.134
I did not know you shared
your lord husband's love...

416
00:24:30.101 --> 00:24:33.103
for the histories.

417
00:24:33.104 --> 00:24:37.942
If not his love. then certainly
an... an abiding interest.

418
00:24:37.943 --> 00:24:39.777
The voices of history
guided Viserys.

419
00:24:39.778 --> 00:24:41.712
He knew that his wisdom alone

420
00:24:41.713 --> 00:24:42.948
could only reach so far.

421
00:24:43.215 --> 00:24:45.951
Do you think that is why
he changed his mind...

422
00:24:47.219 --> 00:24:48.687
in the end?

423
00:24:49.654 --> 00:24:53.591
No matter how suited he
thought Rhaenyra for the crown.

424
00:24:53.592 --> 00:24:58.229
the. uh. voices of
history. as you say.

425
00:24:58.230 --> 00:25:00.965
would have told him how
the realm would react

426
00:25:00.966 --> 00:25:03.667
- to her succession.
- It was impossible to know what steered his thoughts

427
00:25:03.668 --> 00:25:05.704
in those final hours.

428
00:25:06.771 --> 00:25:09.174
Do you now doubt his intentions?

429
00:25:11.142 --> 00:25:12.410
(sniffles)

430
00:25:14.279 --> 00:25:16.547
(light. tense music playing)

431
00:25:16.548 --> 00:25:19.950
Rhaenyra's supporters will
believe what they wish.

432
00:25:19.951 --> 00:25:22.087
And so will Aegon's.

433
00:25:22.754 --> 00:25:27.191
The war will be fought.
many will die...

434
00:25:27.192 --> 00:25:30.161
and the victor will
eventually ascend the throne.

435
00:25:31.796 --> 00:25:35.700
The significance of Viserys's
intentions died with him.

436
00:25:37.168 --> 00:25:39.237
♪

437
00:25:41.740 --> 00:25:43.842
Yes. it did.

438
00:25:48.847 --> 00:25:50.582
(rain pattering)

439
00:25:55.020 --> 00:25:57.122
(water dripping)

440
00:26:08.233 --> 00:26:11.436
- (indistinct shouting)
- (footsteps)

441
00:26:17.175 --> 00:26:20.211
- (sword unsheathes)
- (grunts)

442
00:26:22.781 --> 00:26:24.916
(heavy breathing)

443
00:26:27.452 --> 00:26:29.154
(footsteps)

444
00:26:31.022 --> 00:26:34.159
(ominous music playing)

445
00:26:46.605 --> 00:26:48.306
(footsteps)

446
00:26:51.543 --> 00:26:53.278
(rain pattering)

447
00:26:56.748 --> 00:26:58.850
(torch clatters)

448
00:27:04.756 --> 00:27:06.858
(eerie sounds)

449
00:27:14.399 --> 00:27:16.501
(heavy breathing)

450
00:27:18.770 --> 00:27:20.404
(frog ribbits)

451
00:27:20.405 --> 00:27:23.173
It's a touch late to be
stalkin' about a strange castle.

452
00:27:23.174 --> 00:27:25.442
putting its people to the sword.

453
00:27:25.443 --> 00:27:26.778
You.

454
00:27:27.879 --> 00:27:30.214
I'm called Alys.

455
00:27:30.215 --> 00:27:31.749
Daemon: Strong?

456
00:27:31.750 --> 00:27:33.051
Rivers.

457
00:27:34.019 --> 00:27:35.153
A bastard.

458
00:27:35.587 --> 00:27:38.256
Once you get to know me.
you'll find I'm not so bad.

459
00:27:38.857 --> 00:27:43.360
- So what are you then? Some kind of maester?
- In a manner of speaking.

460
00:27:43.361 --> 00:27:47.164
I inherited the duties after
the last one fled in the night.

461
00:27:47.165 --> 00:27:50.335
- Fled? Why?
- Just never settled in.

462
00:27:51.236 --> 00:27:52.504
(chuckles)

463
00:27:52.937 --> 00:27:54.939
How are you settling in?

464
00:27:55.473 --> 00:27:58.843
I've come to know the face
of tortured rest well enough.

465
00:27:59.344 --> 00:28:03.148
Sleep can be...
thin in this place.

466
00:28:03.782 --> 00:28:05.984
What would you know of my sleep?

467
00:28:06.885 --> 00:28:10.388
Harrenhal's been cursed since
its first stone was laid.

468
00:28:11.256 --> 00:28:13.757
Black Harren felled the
grove of weirwood trees

469
00:28:13.758 --> 00:28:15.859
that grew on these lands.

470
00:28:15.860 --> 00:28:18.195
Heart trees. imbued with
the spirits of those

471
00:28:18.196 --> 00:28:20.064
who lived long before he came.

472
00:28:20.065 --> 00:28:23.901
- It's said their whispers can still be heard sometimes.
- A midwife's tale.

473
00:28:23.902 --> 00:28:27.906
Mm. the very bed you sleep in
was made from such a heart tree.

474
00:28:29.407 --> 00:28:33.144
Have you experienced
anything... of note?

475
00:28:33.645 --> 00:28:36.147
You are a strange kind of woman.

476
00:28:36.514 --> 00:28:39.249
I'm no woman at
all. I'm a barn owl.

477
00:28:39.250 --> 00:28:41.419
Cursed to live in human form.

478
00:28:42.620 --> 00:28:47.224
(chuckles) So. you've come here
after quarreling with your wife?

479
00:28:47.225 --> 00:28:48.426
What?

480
00:28:49.527 --> 00:28:52.196
You arrive here alone
to claim the castle

481
00:28:52.197 --> 00:28:54.632
and yet. send no ravens.

482
00:28:56.634 --> 00:28:59.337
Do you now plan to
make your own claim?

483
00:28:59.738 --> 00:29:02.072
- Perhaps to prove yourself to her.
- Do not try me

484
00:29:02.073 --> 00:29:03.974
with your insolence. witch.

485
00:29:03.975 --> 00:29:05.843
It's a hard thing.
I imagine. to give

486
00:29:05.844 --> 00:29:09.280
obeisance to one who
replaced you as heir.

487
00:29:11.616 --> 00:29:14.151
And a woman too. A...

488
00:29:14.152 --> 00:29:17.055
girl child you
bounced on your knee.

489
00:29:19.124 --> 00:29:22.025
I mean. does it please you that
her legitimacy is contested?

490
00:29:22.026 --> 00:29:24.094
As you stand here...

491
00:29:24.095 --> 00:29:26.663
with a castle and a dragon...

492
00:29:26.664 --> 00:29:29.134
attempting to draw
an army of men.

493
00:29:34.105 --> 00:29:35.840
Here. Drink this.

494
00:29:37.475 --> 00:29:41.412
You'll need your sleep if you're
to win this place to your side.

495
00:29:43.314 --> 00:29:45.416
♪

496
00:29:48.086 --> 00:29:49.554
(swallows)

497
00:29:50.622 --> 00:29:52.322
Willem Blackwood: (muffled)
I now rule my house as regent

498
00:29:52.323 --> 00:29:54.359
until my nephew
Benjicot comes of age.

499
00:29:59.564 --> 00:30:02.566
The Brackens are venal cravens.

500
00:30:02.567 --> 00:30:03.967
and they must pay
for their treachery

501
00:30:03.968 --> 00:30:06.437
against the laws
of gods and men.

502
00:30:07.438 --> 00:30:09.573
(normal) And
against the crown.

503
00:30:09.574 --> 00:30:10.941
Who are you?

504
00:30:10.942 --> 00:30:12.709
Simon: Ser Willem Blackwood
of House Blackwood.

505
00:30:12.710 --> 00:30:15.947
Your Grace. as I said.

506
00:30:19.684 --> 00:30:20.985
Well met.

507
00:30:21.886 --> 00:30:23.620
What might I do for you?

508
00:30:23.621 --> 00:30:27.357
It was you who summoned
me. Your Grace.

509
00:30:27.358 --> 00:30:29.126
I was given to understand

510
00:30:29.127 --> 00:30:30.961
that you wanted an army.

511
00:30:30.962 --> 00:30:32.696
Well. who doesn't these days?

512
00:30:32.697 --> 00:30:34.631
You Blackwoods certainly
never miss a chance

513
00:30:34.632 --> 00:30:38.769
to bloody your
swords... do you?

514
00:30:38.770 --> 00:30:39.937
Some 20 years ago.

515
00:30:39.938 --> 00:30:41.972
my lord bent the
knee to King Viserys

516
00:30:41.973 --> 00:30:45.442
and acknowledged the Princess
Rhaenyra as his rightful heir.

517
00:30:45.443 --> 00:30:47.144
Daemon: So you fight
for this old oath?

518
00:30:47.145 --> 00:30:50.515
Not. of course. for your
thousand-year-old feud with the Brackens.

519
00:30:52.016 --> 00:30:54.619
I once vied for Queen
Rhaenyra's hand...

520
00:30:55.186 --> 00:30:57.155
before she wed Ser Laenor.

521
00:30:57.689 --> 00:30:59.891
I always liked her spirit.

522
00:31:00.358 --> 00:31:02.125
She had the true
blood of the dragon.

523
00:31:02.126 --> 00:31:06.531
And you're prepared to march
without the leave of your lord...

524
00:31:08.399 --> 00:31:11.536
(ominous music playing)

525
00:31:12.437 --> 00:31:14.539
(eerie sounds)

526
00:31:26.651 --> 00:31:28.585
(pouring wine)

527
00:31:28.586 --> 00:31:30.622
Willem: Your Grace?

528
00:31:31.823 --> 00:31:33.457
And once you and your dragon

529
00:31:33.458 --> 00:31:36.794
bring the queen's justice
to the Brackens...

530
00:31:37.161 --> 00:31:39.297
our armies will be yours.

531
00:31:48.239 --> 00:31:50.908
Larys: Our lords in the
Crownlands are grousing.

532
00:31:50.909 --> 00:31:52.876
Their herds of livestock
struggle to keep pace

533
00:31:52.877 --> 00:31:54.578
with the dragons'
relentless appetites.

534
00:31:54.579 --> 00:31:57.014
- Vhagar's in particular.
- Ironrod: They can either provide

535
00:31:57.015 --> 00:32:00.217
the crown what it needs. or
we can claim their holdings.

536
00:32:00.218 --> 00:32:01.785
Tyland Lannister: Oh.
that would be a relief.

537
00:32:01.786 --> 00:32:04.254
as we have no more coin
to lend to the effort.

538
00:32:04.255 --> 00:32:06.490
Resources are certainly
growing no more plentiful

539
00:32:06.491 --> 00:32:07.991
in the face of the blockade.

540
00:32:07.992 --> 00:32:10.060
Tyland: The demand on the
blacksmiths. armorers and tanners

541
00:32:10.061 --> 00:32:11.361
for equipment has
only grown apace

542
00:32:11.362 --> 00:32:12.729
with Ser Criston's army.

543
00:32:12.730 --> 00:32:14.831
Ironrod: Well. Cole's done
splendidly. at the least.

544
00:32:14.832 --> 00:32:16.733
turning every castle
and army he's faced.

545
00:32:16.734 --> 00:32:19.903
- including Duskendale. gods bless him.
- (Aegon spinning marker)

546
00:32:19.904 --> 00:32:21.905
The Kingmaker.
they're calling him.

547
00:32:21.906 --> 00:32:24.207
And with Aemond and
Vhagar also at the ready.

548
00:32:24.208 --> 00:32:26.644
- we are a formidable opponent.
- (slams marker)

549
00:32:27.845 --> 00:32:29.647
You bore me.

550
00:32:32.383 --> 00:32:34.485
You all bore me.

551
00:32:42.894 --> 00:32:44.996
(door opens)

552
00:32:48.800 --> 00:32:52.869
- (door closes) - Perhaps Ser
Criston will be able to procure

553
00:32:52.870 --> 00:32:54.805
more livestock
through his campaign.

554
00:32:54.806 --> 00:32:57.875
Any coin we can save
will be a welcome bounty.

555
00:33:07.652 --> 00:33:09.019
What are you doing here?

556
00:33:09.020 --> 00:33:10.554
Where are your father's books?

557
00:33:10.555 --> 00:33:12.589
- Aegon Targaryen: I ordered them removed.
- (Alicent sighs)

558
00:33:12.590 --> 00:33:13.824
With no thought to the centuries

559
00:33:13.825 --> 00:33:15.559
of knowledge in those pages.

560
00:33:15.560 --> 00:33:17.729
(birds chirping)

561
00:33:22.266 --> 00:33:24.002
Your Grace.

562
00:33:25.336 --> 00:33:28.206
I removed them. I
didn't burn them.

563
00:33:33.344 --> 00:33:34.578
What is it?

564
00:33:34.579 --> 00:33:37.080
- They don't care what I think.
- (pouring wine)

565
00:33:37.081 --> 00:33:38.649
(sighs)

566
00:33:39.650 --> 00:33:41.885
- Who. Aegon?
- My council.

567
00:33:41.886 --> 00:33:44.054
Cole. Aemond. They
pursue their campaign

568
00:33:44.055 --> 00:33:46.524
without seeking my aid.
or even my thoughts.

569
00:33:49.560 --> 00:33:51.195
What thoughts would you have?

570
00:33:52.530 --> 00:33:54.532
Wh... I'm the king.

571
00:33:57.668 --> 00:34:01.406
Do you think simply wearing the
crown imbues you with wisdom?

572
00:34:07.345 --> 00:34:10.948
Those men at your
council table...

573
00:34:11.816 --> 00:34:13.785
earned their seats.

574
00:34:14.152 --> 00:34:17.454
It was my hope that
(chuckles) once enthroned.

575
00:34:17.455 --> 00:34:20.057
you would honor the
burden of your new duties.

576
00:34:20.058 --> 00:34:21.758
be silent.

577
00:34:21.759 --> 00:34:25.763
and strive to learn from the
more studied minds around you.

578
00:34:26.964 --> 00:34:30.268
In the hope that you might be
half the king your father was.

579
00:34:31.736 --> 00:34:34.305
- Tread carefully.
- Or what?

580
00:34:35.773 --> 00:34:38.842
You'll hang me. as you
did your ratcatchers?

581
00:34:38.843 --> 00:34:42.046
Or have me banished.
as you did your Hand?

582
00:34:43.147 --> 00:34:44.314
I ruled

583
00:34:44.315 --> 00:34:46.683
in your father's absence
throughout his long illness.

584
00:34:46.684 --> 00:34:49.419
and Otto Hightower was as cunning
a statesman as ever lived.

585
00:34:49.420 --> 00:34:54.959
You should humbly be seeking
our opinions and counsel.

586
00:34:57.061 --> 00:34:59.129
You have no idea the
sacrifices that were made

587
00:34:59.130 --> 00:35:02.099
to put you on that throne.

588
00:35:02.100 --> 00:35:05.303
(tense music playing)

589
00:35:06.204 --> 00:35:07.271
Wha...

590
00:35:09.273 --> 00:35:12.143
What would you
have me do. Mother?

591
00:35:13.244 --> 00:35:15.847
Do simply what is needed of you:

592
00:35:17.515 --> 00:35:18.983
nothing.

593
00:35:21.752 --> 00:35:23.821
♪

594
00:35:26.491 --> 00:35:29.760
(ambient nature sounds)

595
00:35:33.764 --> 00:35:35.500
(axe striking)

596
00:35:36.334 --> 00:35:38.436
(tree crackling)

597
00:35:44.675 --> 00:35:47.512
(indistinct chatter. shouting)

598
00:35:48.980 --> 00:35:51.182
Criston: On your feet!

599
00:35:52.350 --> 00:35:54.452
To Rook's Rest!

600
00:35:55.553 --> 00:35:57.054
To battle!

601
00:36:01.993 --> 00:36:03.793
Gwayne Hightower:
It's broad daylight.

602
00:36:03.794 --> 00:36:07.430
We must hold here and ready
ourselves to lay siege at nightfall.

603
00:36:07.431 --> 00:36:09.499
We shall move now
and strike by day.

604
00:36:09.500 --> 00:36:10.867
They will not expect it.

605
00:36:10.868 --> 00:36:12.169
They will not expect it

606
00:36:12.170 --> 00:36:14.539
because it is fucking madness.

607
00:36:16.140 --> 00:36:17.474
Did you forget the
little encounter

608
00:36:17.475 --> 00:36:19.377
we had on the road to Rosby?

609
00:36:19.977 --> 00:36:21.245
I did not.

610
00:36:22.914 --> 00:36:26.184
Dragonstone and their dragons
are just across the bay.

611
00:36:27.385 --> 00:36:29.587
What? Grown tired
of living. have you?

612
00:36:30.421 --> 00:36:32.190
Are you afraid. Ser?

613
00:36:33.057 --> 00:36:35.526
Worse. I'm rational.

614
00:36:37.461 --> 00:36:38.963
We advance.

615
00:36:39.397 --> 00:36:42.533
(tense music playing)

616
00:36:55.646 --> 00:36:57.715
♪

617
00:36:59.350 --> 00:37:01.084
Jacaerys Velaryon: I
see no other choice.

618
00:37:01.085 --> 00:37:03.854
- We need to send a dragon.
- Rhaenyra Targaryen: Where?

619
00:37:07.625 --> 00:37:09.726
(clears throat)
To support the war

620
00:37:09.727 --> 00:37:13.096
that your vassals have been
fighting in your absence...

621
00:37:13.097 --> 00:37:15.465
Your Grace.

622
00:37:15.466 --> 00:37:18.668
Cole's host has grown
since riding abroad.

623
00:37:18.669 --> 00:37:20.870
He raised the levies of
both Rosby and Stokeworth

624
00:37:20.871 --> 00:37:24.007
and. with their combined
strength. sacked Duskendale.

625
00:37:24.008 --> 00:37:25.575
Duskendale?

626
00:37:25.576 --> 00:37:27.544
The city has fallen.

627
00:37:27.545 --> 00:37:29.412
Many Darklyn men
declared for Aegon.

628
00:37:29.413 --> 00:37:31.514
Those who refused
were put to the sword.

629
00:37:31.515 --> 00:37:33.350
What of my father?

630
00:37:33.351 --> 00:37:34.852
He kept his oath.

631
00:37:35.319 --> 00:37:37.288
Cole took his head for it.

632
00:37:39.323 --> 00:37:42.025
Where have you been.
these last days?

633
00:37:42.026 --> 00:37:44.795
You vanished without
so much as a word.

634
00:37:45.363 --> 00:37:48.531
Well. I apologize for my
absence and the secrecy.

635
00:37:48.532 --> 00:37:51.368
but such was necessary.

636
00:37:51.369 --> 00:37:53.604
I went to King's Landing.

637
00:37:54.438 --> 00:37:55.972
To what possible end?

638
00:37:55.973 --> 00:37:58.341
To meet Queen Alicent
and sue for peace.

639
00:37:58.342 --> 00:38:01.144
- You saw Alicent?
- Rhaenyra: Yes. I did.

640
00:38:01.145 --> 00:38:03.446
You could've been
taken or slain!

641
00:38:03.447 --> 00:38:07.484
I inherited 80 years of
peace from my father.

642
00:38:07.485 --> 00:38:09.052
Before I was to end it.

643
00:38:09.053 --> 00:38:12.356
I needed to know that
there was no other path.

644
00:38:14.825 --> 00:38:16.527
And now I do.

645
00:38:19.964 --> 00:38:21.865
Only one choice remains to me:

646
00:38:21.866 --> 00:38:26.370
either I win my claim or die.

647
00:38:27.872 --> 00:38:30.107
We stand at the ready.

648
00:38:30.841 --> 00:38:33.243
Rhaenys Targaryen: Cole's
victories have only emboldened him.

649
00:38:33.244 --> 00:38:35.378
He marches on Rook's Rest.

650
00:38:35.379 --> 00:38:36.846
His host was just hours away

651
00:38:36.847 --> 00:38:40.183
- when Lord Staunton's ravens took wing.
- Why Rook's Rest?

652
00:38:40.184 --> 00:38:41.484
After Duskendale?

653
00:38:41.485 --> 00:38:43.520
It is but a small coastal keep.

654
00:38:43.521 --> 00:38:47.223
Alfred: 'Cause Lord Staunton
is a member of this council.

655
00:38:47.224 --> 00:38:51.328
And because his castle is small and
vulnerable and there for the taking.

656
00:38:51.329 --> 00:38:53.763
Cole knows we have no
army on the mainland.

657
00:38:53.764 --> 00:38:56.399
- Bartimos: He is brazen.
- He is daring us to act.

658
00:38:56.400 --> 00:38:59.436
We need to send a dragon.

659
00:38:59.437 --> 00:39:02.873
(quiet. tense music playing)

660
00:39:06.310 --> 00:39:10.581
There are those who have
mistaken my caution for weakness.

661
00:39:15.052 --> 00:39:17.887
Let that be their undoing.

662
00:39:17.888 --> 00:39:20.056
- I will go.
- My queen...

663
00:39:20.057 --> 00:39:22.959
- You cannot.
- I will not lose dragons to war

664
00:39:22.960 --> 00:39:24.294
whilst I hide here in my castle.

665
00:39:24.295 --> 00:39:27.564
Our allies raise their
banners for you. Mother.

666
00:39:27.565 --> 00:39:29.599
Rhaenyra: Yes. they do.

667
00:39:29.600 --> 00:39:32.769
If you die. all is lost.

668
00:39:32.770 --> 00:39:34.170
- Send me.
- No.

669
00:39:34.171 --> 00:39:36.239
I will burn Cole's lines and
withdraw before King's Landing

670
00:39:36.240 --> 00:39:38.440
- could even raise the alarm.
- You lack the experience.

671
00:39:41.245 --> 00:39:43.714
You must send me. Your Grace.

672
00:39:45.783 --> 00:39:47.217
Meleys is your largest dragon

673
00:39:47.218 --> 00:39:49.420
and no stranger to battle.

674
00:39:52.089 --> 00:39:54.024
I will meet Cole.

675
00:39:54.825 --> 00:39:55.992
(sighs)

676
00:39:55.993 --> 00:39:58.129
♪

677
00:40:17.782 --> 00:40:19.884
♪

678
00:40:42.206 --> 00:40:43.941
(flagon shatters)

679
00:40:45.376 --> 00:40:47.445
♪

680
00:41:02.426 --> 00:41:04.327
Jacaerys: I wish only
to fight for you.

681
00:41:04.328 --> 00:41:06.463
for your claim and mine.

682
00:41:06.464 --> 00:41:08.032
I...

683
00:41:09.233 --> 00:41:11.135
There's something I
need to tell you. Jace.

684
00:41:13.504 --> 00:41:16.840
Something... I
should've told you

685
00:41:16.841 --> 00:41:20.176
when you first became
heir to the throne.

686
00:41:20.177 --> 00:41:23.246
It's a secret that
Viserys told me

687
00:41:23.247 --> 00:41:25.683
when he named me his successor.

688
00:41:26.484 --> 00:41:29.687
And it has passed
from king to heir...

689
00:41:30.354 --> 00:41:33.390
since Aegon the
Conqueror's time.

690
00:41:35.826 --> 00:41:37.528
(exhales)

691
00:41:38.863 --> 00:41:40.865
♪

692
00:41:41.465 --> 00:41:43.867
I never told you
because I was unsure

693
00:41:43.868 --> 00:41:46.036
that I believed it myself.

694
00:41:46.837 --> 00:41:50.707
The Targaryen who
sits the Iron Throne

695
00:41:50.708 --> 00:41:53.209
is not just a king or a queen.

696
00:41:53.210 --> 00:41:55.645
They are a Protector.

697
00:41:55.646 --> 00:41:57.848
{\an8}(speaking High Valyrian)

698
00:41:59.316 --> 00:42:01.651
Rhaenyra: Ordained to
lead the Seven Kingdoms.

699
00:42:01.652 --> 00:42:03.052
to strengthen them...

700
00:42:03.053 --> 00:42:05.355
(indistinct shouting)

701
00:42:05.356 --> 00:42:09.693
and to unite them
against a common foe.

702
00:42:14.031 --> 00:42:17.434
Viserys chose me to succeed him.

703
00:42:18.269 --> 00:42:21.104
He held to this the
whole of his life.

704
00:42:21.105 --> 00:42:22.873
(shouting)

705
00:42:26.544 --> 00:42:30.146
My father believed
that I. alone.

706
00:42:30.147 --> 00:42:32.782
was meant to be this Protector.

707
00:42:32.783 --> 00:42:36.052
They're 1.400-. 1.500-strong
at least. my lord.

708
00:42:36.053 --> 00:42:37.420
(roars)

709
00:42:37.421 --> 00:42:38.888
Rhaenyra: But to
unite the realm.

710
00:42:38.889 --> 00:42:41.759
I had to send the
dragons to war.

711
00:42:42.393 --> 00:42:43.793
(roars)

712
00:42:43.794 --> 00:42:45.930
♪

713
00:42:49.567 --> 00:42:53.537
The horrors I have just loosed
cannot be for a crown alone.

714
00:42:55.506 --> 00:42:57.440
That is why I must believe

715
00:42:57.441 --> 00:43:00.677
what Viserys told me when
he named me his heir.

716
00:43:00.678 --> 00:43:03.080
What Jaehaerys had told him.

717
00:43:03.747 --> 00:43:06.215
And what I will now tell you.

718
00:43:06.216 --> 00:43:08.385
(Sunfyre calls)

719
00:43:08.953 --> 00:43:10.019
What is it?

720
00:43:10.020 --> 00:43:12.156
♪

721
00:43:16.327 --> 00:43:18.662
Aegon the Conqueror's Dream.

722
00:43:20.631 --> 00:43:24.335
He called it "The
Song of Ice and Fire."

723
00:43:24.802 --> 00:43:28.538
{\an8}- (dramatic music playing)
- (arrows whizzing by)

724
00:43:28.539 --> 00:43:30.774
(grunting. shouting)

725
00:43:34.078 --> 00:43:36.280
captain: Loose! New rank!

726
00:43:37.381 --> 00:43:40.484
Loose! New rank!

727
00:43:41.485 --> 00:43:43.954
Loose! New rank!

728
00:43:46.156 --> 00:43:48.524
♪

729
00:43:48.525 --> 00:43:49.660
Push it!

730
00:43:50.661 --> 00:43:52.562
Guards (shouting): Dragon!

731
00:43:52.563 --> 00:43:54.764
Dragon!

732
00:43:54.765 --> 00:43:56.934
(all yelling)

733
00:43:58.535 --> 00:44:01.205
Gwayne: To the Seven
Hells with you. Cole!

734
00:44:01.572 --> 00:44:03.873
You may as well have sounded
horns to announce our coming!

735
00:44:03.874 --> 00:44:06.009
Criston: Order the Darklyn levies
to break off and move ahead.

736
00:44:06.010 --> 00:44:07.977
We must keep the dragon's
attention divided.

737
00:44:07.978 --> 00:44:10.013
- Make the signal.
- What signal?

738
00:44:10.014 --> 00:44:12.616
Criston: All is going to plan.

739
00:44:13.250 --> 00:44:15.319
♪

740
00:44:18.756 --> 00:44:20.858
(blows horn)

741
00:44:22.059 --> 00:44:23.794
(growling)

742
00:44:32.703 --> 00:44:34.838
(indistinct shouting)

743
00:44:38.942 --> 00:44:41.045
(all yelling)

744
00:44:44.581 --> 00:44:46.917
(horn blowing in distance)

745
00:44:48.052 --> 00:44:50.453
(blows horn)

746
00:44:50.454 --> 00:44:52.222
(growling)

747
00:44:56.126 --> 00:44:58.195
♪

748
00:45:01.899 --> 00:45:04.001
(Sunfyre calls)

749
00:45:06.303 --> 00:45:07.771
(groans)

750
00:45:09.406 --> 00:45:11.175
{\an8}(speaking High Valyrian)

751
00:45:19.850 --> 00:45:21.552
(exhales)

752
00:45:23.020 --> 00:45:25.089
♪

753
00:45:25.789 --> 00:45:27.124
(screeches)

754
00:45:32.196 --> 00:45:33.897
(grumbles)

755
00:45:35.532 --> 00:45:37.634
(all yelling)

756
00:45:39.703 --> 00:45:42.239
♪

757
00:45:44.141 --> 00:45:45.708
Forward. Sunfyre!

758
00:45:45.709 --> 00:45:48.045
- (Sunfyre roars)
- Faster!

759
00:45:48.479 --> 00:45:50.546
Guards (shouting): Dragon!

760
00:45:50.547 --> 00:45:52.615
Whose dragon is that?

761
00:45:52.616 --> 00:45:54.451
His Grace. the king's.

762
00:45:55.419 --> 00:45:57.553
This was your secret plot. Cole?

763
00:45:57.554 --> 00:45:59.288
For the king himself
to lay ambush

764
00:45:59.289 --> 00:46:01.657
- and mayhaps die in the attempt?!
- Criston: No!

765
00:46:01.658 --> 00:46:03.727
Loose more signal arrows!

766
00:46:06.930 --> 00:46:09.433
Stalwart men of House Targaryen.

767
00:46:10.534 --> 00:46:13.070
your king has joined you!

768
00:46:13.837 --> 00:46:16.606
Hold to your courage!
Hold to your wits!

769
00:46:16.607 --> 00:46:19.408
For the Seven have
blessed and shielded

770
00:46:19.409 --> 00:46:21.878
this host with divine purpose!

771
00:46:21.879 --> 00:46:24.814
For the one true king. Aegon!

772
00:46:24.815 --> 00:46:27.651
- Advance!
- (soldiers shouting)

773
00:46:29.386 --> 00:46:32.956
♪

774
00:46:35.659 --> 00:46:37.861
Where are you. Aemond?

775
00:46:41.098 --> 00:46:42.800
(roars)

776
00:46:44.268 --> 00:46:46.336
♪

777
00:46:49.573 --> 00:46:51.708
{\an8}(speaks High Valyrian)

778
